class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkTerminalAction\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkTerminalAction</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">action</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkTerminalAction","kind":"def","line":590,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkTerminalAction","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.lean#L590-L591"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkSeq\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkSeq</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">action</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkSeq","kind":"def","line":587,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkSeq","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.lean#L587-L588"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkReassignCore\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkReassignCore</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">xs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.Var\">Var</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">stx</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Extending code blocks with reassignments: `x : t := v` and `x : t ← v`.\nRemark: `stx` is the syntax for the declaration (e.g., `letDecl`), and `xs` are the variables\ndeclared by it. It is an array because we have let-declarations that declare multiple variables.\nExample: `(x, y) ← t`\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkReassignCore","kind":"def","line":573,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkReassignCore","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.lean#L573-L585"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkVarDeclCore\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkVarDeclCore</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">xs</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.Var\">Var</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">stx</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.Syntax\">Syntax</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Extending code blocks with variable declarations: `let x : t := v` and `let x : t ← v`.\nWe remove `x` from the collection of updated variables.\nRemark: `stx` is the syntax for the declaration (e.g., `letDecl`), and `xs` are the variables\ndeclared by it. It is an array because we have let-declarations that declare multiple variables.\nExample: `let (x, y) := t`\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkVarDeclCore","kind":"def","line":561,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Do.mkVarDeclCore","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.lean#L561-L571"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.homogenize\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">homogenize</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">c₂</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> (<a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Prod\">×</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a>)</span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Given two code blocks `c₁` and `c₂`, make sure they have the same set of updated variables.\nLet `ws` the union of the updated variables in `c₁‵ and ‵c₂`.\nWe use `extendUpdatedVars c₁ ws` and `extendUpdatedVars c₂ ws`\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.homogenize","kind":"def","line":550,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Do.homogenize","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.lean#L550-L559"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.extendUpdatedVars\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">extendUpdatedVars</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ws</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.VarSet\">VarSet</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.CodeBlock\">CodeBlock</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Extend the set of updated variables. It assumes `ws` is a super set of `c.uvars`.\nWe **cannot** simply update the field `c.uvars`, because `c` may have shadowed some variable in `ws`.\nSee discussion at `pullExitPoints`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.extendUpdatedVars","kind":"def","line":535,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Do.extendUpdatedVars","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.lean#L535-L545"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.extendUpdatedVarsAux\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">extendUpdatedVarsAux</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.Code\">Code</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">ws</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.VarSet\">VarSet</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.Code\">Code</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.extendUpdatedVarsAux","kind":"def","line":499,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Do.extendUpdatedVarsAux","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.lean#L499-L533"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.pullExitPoints\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">pullExitPoints</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.Code\">Code</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.Code\">Code</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Auxiliary operation for adding new variables to the collection of updated variables in a CodeBlock.\nWhen a new variable is not already in the collection, but is shadowed by some declaration in `c`,\nwe create auxiliary join points to make sure we preserve the semantics of the code block.\nExample: suppose we have the code block `print x; let x := 10; return x`. And we want to extend it\nwith the reassignment `x := x + 1`. We first use `pullExitPoints` to create\n```\nlet jp (x!1) :=  return x!1;\nprint x;\nlet x := 10;\njmp jp x\n```\nand then we add the reassignment\n```\nx := x + 1\nlet jp (x!1) := return x!1;\nprint x;\nlet x := 10;\njmp jp x\n```\nNote that we created a fresh variable `x!1` to avoid accidental name capture.\nAs another example, consider\n```\nprint x;\nlet x := 10\ny := y + 1;\nreturn x;\n```\nWe transform it into\n```\nlet jp (y x!1) := return x!1;\nprint x;\nlet x := 10\ny := y + 1;\njmp jp y x\n```\nand then we add the reassignment as in the previous example.\nWe need to include `y` in the jump, because each exit point is implicitly returning the set of\nupdate variables.\n\nWe implement the method as follows. Let `us` be `c.uvars`, then\n1- for each `return _ y` in `c`, we create a join point\n  `let j (us y!1) := return y!1`\n   and replace the `return _ y` with `jmp us y`\n2- for each `break`, we create a join point\n  `let j (us) := break`\n   and replace the `break` with `jmp us`.\n3- Same as 2 for `continue`.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.pullExitPoints","kind":"def","line":443,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Do.pullExitPoints","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5dce5a5c26591c31cb697/src/Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.lean#L443-L497"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">partial def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.pullExitPointsAux\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Elab</span>.<span class=\"name\">Term</span>.<span class=\"name\">Do</span>.<span class=\"name\">pullExitPointsAux</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">rs</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.VarSet\">VarSet</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">c</span> : <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.Code\">Code</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Control/StateRef.html#StateRefT'\">StateRefT'</a> <a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO.RealWorld\">IO.RealWorld</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Array\">Array</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.JPDecl\">JPDecl</a>)</span> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Term/TermElabM.html#Lean.Elab.Term.TermElabM\">TermElabM</a> <a href=\"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.Code\">Code</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"`pullExitPointsAux rs c` auxiliary method for `pullExitPoints`, `rs` is the set of update variable in the current path.  ","docLink":"./Lean/Elab/Do/Legacy.html#Lean.Elab.Term.Do.pullExitPointsAux","kind":"opaque","line":418,"name":"Lean.Elab.Term.Do.pullExitPointsAux","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/b4812ae53eea93439ad5d